        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no known chronic medical illnesses and no prior psychiatric hospitalizations. Over the past year, she has experienced increasing academic pressure, conflict with peers, and distress related to feeling socially excluded. Her mother reports a gradual shift from a previously engaged, creative teenager to someone more isolated, fatigued, and self-critical over the last 8 to 10 weeks. There is no history of mania, psychosis, head injury, or substance misuse.\n\n{patientName} was seen once in the emergency department earlier this year after disclosing passive suicidal thoughts to a school counselor; she was discharged home with a safety plan and outpatient follow-up. She has not previously taken antidepressants. Sleep has been poor, often 4 to 5 fragmented hours on school nights. She skips breakfast, eats lightly during the day, and has reduced participation in exercise since stopping soccer. Immunizations are up to date, and developmental history is otherwise unremarkable."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
